Abstract: As darkness shrouded the fields, Bill Lenschow milked the cows and finished his chores, then sat down with his wife, Kathy, to a special dinner of steak and shrimp.    With lights blazing in their house on Washington Place, the Newquist children played bingo and card games with their parents, Tammy and Howard.
